******
[2] Ecuador (Quito)
Date: Mon 10 Oct 2010
Source: El Comercio [in Spanish, trans. by Mod.MMP, edited]
http://www.elcomercio.com/sociedad/virus-sarampion-proviene-Minnesota-EEUU_0_569943058.html


There are already 86 confirmed cases of measles in Ecuador, 83
(including 2 from genotype B2 which is circulating in Africa and the
United States) have been reported in the province of Tunguragua and 3
in Quito. This information was provided by the Ecudorian Minister of
Health, David Chiriboga, this morning [10 Oct 2011]. There are 2
suspected cases in Guayaquil, who are being followed. According to the
Minister, the outbreak was provoked by a virus that arrived from
Minnesota in the United States and that the virus has not been endemic
in Ecuador since 1997. In Minnesota, there was an outbreak of measles
last May [2011].

Last week, Ecuador began a national vaccination campaign in response
to this outbreak, that according to the Minister of Health David
Chiroga "is due to a virus that usually circulated in Africa and the
United States, and which probably came to the country with some person
who travelled outside of the country [Ecuador]."

