[Wellington is the capital city and 3rd most populous urban area of
New Zealand. It is at the southwestern tip of the North Island,
between Cook Strait and the Rimutaka Range. The Wellington urban area
is the major population centre of the southern North Island. The
location of Wellington is shown in the HealthMap/ProMED-mail
interactive map of New Zealand at: http://healthmap.org/r/1kSd.

Reports of cases of measles virus infection in previously unaffected
areas are declining with the exception of Ecuador and New Zealand. The
vast number of cases in various parts of the African continent remain
under-reported.

In New Zealand, Auckland remains the centre of a serious and spreading
outbreak. The upcoming deciding game in the Rugby World cup, to be
played in Auckland on 23 Oct 2011 featuring a Northern hemisphere
country (France) and a Southern hemisphere country (New Zealand), may
prolong and disseminate this outbreak. - Mod.CP]
